details.description: Here at Waterbean Coffee, we always try to stay original and never follow the trends. In a time when most coffee shops focus on getting the customers in and out of their doors the quickest, we try to give them a place to relax, hold meetings, go over schoolwork, or just hang out with friends. We want to be more than just another coffee shop.

reviews_data.review_text: Went here visiting my sister and stopped in. Got the snickers doodle latte and its so delicious! Cute place too!
A plethora of gluten free options!
Great Place and very friendly employees!! I have always had a wonderful experience here.
great coffee, great food, wonderful staff! the place is clean & well lit! the staff knew what they were doing & helped me make an excellent choice!

Waterbean Coffee is so cute and in a perfect location. I have had many chai tea lattes, but this iced one with brown sugar… unmatched. There wasn’t a long wait, lots of options, and they even have a gelato selection. Perfect place for a sweet treat!

review_questions.Seating type: Indoor dining area, Outdoor patio / terrace, Private dining room

reviews_data.review_text: Baristas are always nice and welcoming. Food and drinks are great, and love the atmosphere
Every time I come here after work, it’s always a good visit that I am content with! I really, really love their iced chai tea—it’s a favorite!

I’m a regular at the Cornelius Waterbean and truly appreciate their consistently great coffee—I’ll always support local spots like this. However, I’ve noticed a big difference when visiting the Davidson location. While the coffee remains excellent, the overall customer experience could use improvement.

The baristas often seem disengaged and unapproachable, which really affects the vibe. Having worked in a coffee shop that is voted Best in NC year after year, I understand how important it is to greet every customer warmly, even when you’re in the middle of a task. A simple “hello” can go a long way in making someone feel welcome. Unfortunately, that energy is missing here.

I’d love to see the Davidson team bring the same level of friendliness and hospitality that makes the Cornelius location such a great spot.

Today, I had a freakish experience at this location of Waterbean Coffee--the first time in my entire life. I ordered a small latte for $5.41, made the payment using Apple Pay, and then went to look for a seat. When I got home, I found that the barista tipped herself $1 (see the screenshot, at 15:47, April 23, 2025) following my payment. I clearly remember I didn't wait for the tip options to be shown on the POS screen as it took a bit longer than normal, and some cafes no longer have the tip options for coffee.

Although it was only one dollar, which could have passed unnoticed, it gives me a negative feeling about this cafe as a whole, and I'm not motivated to revisit it. One dollar doesn't matter at all, but honesty and decency matter more in keeping loyal customers going back. The barista did that without the customer knowing and without the customer’s consent. I hope that this review will serve as a warning for the future.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi M. L., We’re very sorry about what happened today. This is not reflective of our values, and if it was done intentionally, it will not be tolerated. We’ll issue you a full refund right away including your ordered. We will look into this situation. Please email us your information at info@waterbeancoffee.com so we can follow up. Thank you.

reviews_data.review_text: Small and cozy. Very nice

The barista was clearly having a bad day. Seemed annoyed to take our order, threw dishes around in the back to the point where everyone in the shop stopped talking and looked up. Asked for more half and half in the container and she threw more dishes around and put a splash in rather than refilling the entire container. Not sure what was going on but I felt embarrassed for her and a little sad at whatever was going on. I hope things get better for her as clearly she’s going through it.
Rude barista. Ordered our drinks and the barista got our order wrong. When she was told, she was mad. Took it back, remade, then plopped on counter and walked away. Won’t go back.
Lots of tasty menus!

review_questions.Vegetarian offerings: Menu is all vegetarian, Large vegetarian selection

reviews_data.review_text: Cozy location with good coffee and a decent selection of baked goods. Friendly staff and ample parking. Of all the Waterbean locations, this one has the best vibe. Note, there is also ice cream available here. Good seating for solo work, meeting between two people, plus there is a larger table in the back for a group.
Just like the other WaterBean I've visited - food and drinks are excellent, and the atmosphere is cute and comfortable.
Great place to go work on your laptop, lots of room.
Great Coffee and Atmosphere!
